cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with modelling the interactions of two sentences using deep neural networks. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new deep architecture for modelling sentence pairs. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of deep learning techniques to model natural language interactions. It may also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses LSTMs, a type of neural network, to model sentence interactions. Finally, it could be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as dynamic pooling is used to select the most informative features, which is a common technique in computer vision.
